There was no system with Elder members mentioned.  That was simply saying &quot;If you said elder members were important, then you could have them have tags.&quot;  That's all.  This point is moot because it doesn't matter.<br>
<br>
Let's talk about what officers &quot;do behind the scenes&quot; as you say, and how any member would and could do that.<br>
<br>
Forums- what I gather from this, is that you're saying only officers have the ability to work HTML and set up a page or a broadcasting system for the guild.  I could make a forum for the guild, if you really want to.  All I have to do is go to MSN.  I could even manage it.  That doesn't necessarily mean I'm an officer of the guild.<br>
<br>
E-mails- if everyone sent out a welcome e-mail to everyone, it would be much better than one person sending a welcome e-mail, at least it's more welcming =).  Why can't a normal person do this, is that illegal?  How many people do *you* know of that *aren't* officers and don't send welcoming e-mails.  Another thing that you don't need an officer for.  Besides, half the time no one knows whether or not someone is new or an alt.  If you need an officer for that then they haven't been on top of it.<br>
<br>
Guildmotd- The person who made the guild, of course.  If you need more, than give everyone the power to change it.  How come only officers are the ones who can set raids or motd up.  Doesn't everyone have something important to say?<br>
<br>
Invite- Once again, name everyone an officer and you don't have &quot;officer powers.&quot;  This is merely an issue of getting past the coding.  If you need specific rules before someone can join, set those down.  You've got it.  That way you dont have a bunch of random people joining and leaving.<br>
<br>
Exterior Relations- Anyone holds relations, you admit that when you threaten to kick those who dont follow GCP.  You dont need someone special for this, that's rediculous.  You especially don't need someone special to set up a raid.  It's that mindset that I hate.<br>
<br>
Back to Forums- Starting with the quote &quot;We hash out the details of said topic and THEN give it to the guild for more input.&quot;  Didn't the Nazi's do the same thing with their media.  And the Russians too?  Doesn't mean it's necessarily a good/safe idea.  You don't let people touch the juicy parts.<br>
<br>
Now you say that officers dont have much power, but you know that's not necessarily true.  Even Deloit admitted this.  It's an implied power.  People will more naturally believe an officer over anyone else.  The same is with your &quot;intra guild&quot; relationships.  <br>
<br>
The fact is, in most points you give, Athame, an officer is *not* necessary for that particular role.  Anyone can do that.  They just feel restricted because you have the officer tag *outside* of the game.  If everyone in the guild had it, you wouldn't have the invite problems, the guildmotd problems, and everyone would be equal.  Right?<br>
<br>
And once again, I apologize when I say AoL doesn't go on raids.  I dont mean they never do, I mean they dont raid every night, every day, and they really can't do powerful raids.  Unless you'd like to correct me by doing plane of air, if any of you are flagged for that.<br>
<br>
