<br>
If you honestly follow the mindset that an officer must be a raid leader than you only feed my position.  I'm not saying you do it Athame, I respect you a lot as an officer, but can you account for every officer in the guild when I say &quot;some abuse their title?&quot; I dont think so. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#A0B0E0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/bthearrowoflightcommons.showUserPublicProfile?gid=meowkatdarklingborn>Meowkat Darklingborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#000080>(6/9/03 6:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Thread Deletion</span><hr size=1> Sorry for the spam, by the way, but I also forgot to mention my specific reason.<br>
<br>
I feel that Ariaya over extended her powers as an officer, or maybe as a normal person. <br>
<br>
I asked in guild if anyone could help me with a transfer.  I needed to get 800 pp to Jerika, but Meowkat was in a dangerous place and didn't want to hurt anyone, so I asked if I could snag the 800pp to make the trade I was going to engage in, and Xeno said he'd have no problem with it.  I thanked him.  While he was camping, Ariaya starts in on me asking question after question about what my trade was going to be and why I needed the money. <br>
<br>
That puts me in a very bad position for the type of person I am.  I love people, but only when I want to.  And I don't feel like I have to explain myself to someone.<br>
<br>
Now, had I said to Ariaya, &quot;What I do with the money is my business and the person who is letting me snag it until I can get Meow out&quot; I would have been put up for a &quot;questioning&quot; type of circumstance of being rude to Ariaya.  Instead, I basically felt I had to persist through her questions that I dont want to answer.  No, I dont trust Ariaya and feel like I have to explain myself to her.  I don't know her, and just because she has a tag doesn't mean I should have to tell her what's going on.  In fact, I never signed anything that said that.  That's why it's a bad position.  I had three options- answer her questions for no reason what so ever and feel pushed around, not answer her questions in a rude manner, or avoiding getting people upset with one another because of what happened and avoiding getting kicked for being rude to an officer by dropping out of the guild.  <br>
<br>
Sorry, that's the type of person I am.  If I've never been hunting with you or if you don't make a point to talk to me, I don't make it a point in my &quot;in game&quot; time to actually set about and try to make friends with you either.  <br>
<br>
I say deal with it.  Deloit says Ariaya was wrong.  But how could I have said that she was without being a jerk?  Instead, I dropped out.<br>
<br>
How's that for specifics?  Probably bad.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E6E8fA><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/bthearrowoflightcommons.showUserPublicProfile?gid=twoxenos>TwoXenos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Two Xenos! One LOW price!</span><br>  Posts: 201<br> <font color=#000080>(6/9/03 7:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Thread Deletion</span><hr size=1> Meowkat:  I've never had any trouble with you before, but I think that you've handled this whole situation very poorly.  I don't think its ok to say &quot;that's just the kind of person I am&quot;; I think we should all do our best to always treat others with thoughtfulness, even if they do not return the favor.<br>
<br>
As far as the raiding comments go, I have a few thoughts:<br>
<br>
1.  I would agree with the statement that we are not a raiding guild.  This doesn't mean that we don't host raids, just not 4 nights a week.  And I don't expect my /who guild all to ever show &quot;timea&quot; after anyone's name.<br>
  <br>
2.  This also doesn't mean that we don't raid with other guilds.  If you are interested in raiding more, being a member of AoL does give you a great outlet for raiding through the GCP.  It's true that we don't form up as a guild to join these raids; we let each member decide how often and where and with whom they want to raid.  You just need to take the initiative to sign up; Sytox has a very nice GCP FAQ stickied in the members forum, and there are four (4) GCP links at the top of the boards page.<br>
<br>
3.  To take a couple of your specific examples, I for one do raid with SS on a regular basis (generally at least once a week).  This coming Saturday I'll be joining them in the Plane of Air; I've been to Hate with them a number of times, and in fact I've even raided CT (another of your examples) with SS.  I'm not alone in this; most raids have people from a variety of guilds joining together to do things that we otherwise couldn't do.<br>
<br>
